        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-31T17:55:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suspect the field named \u0027cpsr\u0027 in Fuchsia probably really is \u0027pstate\u0027, but from looking at https://developer.arm.com/products/architecture/cpu-architecture/a-profile/docs/100878/latest/processor-state it seems like they\u0027re not the same thing; cpsr probably having been copied from 32bit ARM definition? Perhaps a rename of the Fuchsia one is warranted, or at least a TODO+bug upstream to investigate.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 58,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "99806be875af6d32d20e1af8347385ec412651f8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "15351f49_1267da8b",
        "filename": "snapshot/fuchsia/cpu_context_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 58,
      "author": {
        "id": 1311398
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-31T18:25:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No. The actual register being outputted as a view of the pstate is spsr masked for userspace:\nhttps://fuchsia.googlesource.com/zircon/+/master/kernel/arch/arm64/debugger.cpp#43\n\nI agree that naming it cpsr is misleading, but I wonder how much code outside of zircon depends on this and if it\u0027s worth making a transition for this. At the very least we should comment it.",
      "parentUuid": "89d7018f_cf5af443",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 58,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "99806be875af6d32d20e1af8347385ec412651f8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "993c619f_bd109440",
        "filename": "snapshot/fuchsia/cpu_context_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 58,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-31T18:37:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for checking Cristian.\n\nIt looks like Josh was banging around in ARM64 contexts recently in breakpad too https://github.com/google/breakpad/tree/master/src/tools/linux/md2core and maybe has thoughts or pro-tips.\n\nSo... skimming around (my knowledge of ARM is very limited, sorry) https://developer.arm.com/products/architecture/cpu-architecture/a-profile/docs/100878/latest/the-saved-process-status-register it seems like we\u0027re only expecting to get NZCV, something like this would probably be appropriate:\n\nconstexpr uint64_t kNZXV \u003d 0xf0000000;\n// ... stuff describing our various confusions ...\ncontext-\u003epstate \u003d thread_context.cpsr \u0026 kNZCV;\n\n(based on the assumption that spsr and pstate store those bits in the same place.)\n\nDoes that sound plausible to anyone?",
      "parentUuid": "15351f49_1267da8b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 58,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "99806be875af6d32d20e1af8347385ec412651f8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b5b24f47_bbaeda6c",
        "filename": "snapshot/fuchsia/cpu_context_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 58,
      "author": {
        "id": 1311398
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-31T19:45:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "spsr has a defined structure: \nhttp://infocenter.arm.com/help/index.jsp?topic\u003d/com.arm.doc.den0024a/BABHJFEE.html, which seems to be similar to cpsr, so your mask would work. Technically, this is not needed as the kernel already does the same masking, but that is an implementation detail we should not rely on (I don\u0027t think it\u0027s documented). \nThe only bit that is somewhat misleading is the kernel naming of cpsr.",
      "parentUuid": "993c619f_bd109440",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 58,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "99806be875af6d32d20e1af8347385ec412651f8",
